{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The railway track went through the middle of the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These 20 cattle trucks would appear every Monday afternoon.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And on Monday evening, there would be published a list of approximately 1,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they had to report Tuesday morning to go into the cattle trucks for resettlement in the East.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, in Westerbork, we had again the same thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a [INAUDIBLE], a Jewish council, that was set up to administer all these things.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is really where there was more trouble, because Westerbork was a camp that was built before the war by the Dutch government, not by the Germans and the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was before the war, built by the Dutch government for Jewish refugees from Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We came early, in 1936, and we could make our way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But later, people who came from Germany and Austria and all that who got out without money, without furniture, without anything kind of thing-- they didn't have anything, and they were all put into Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these were Jewish refugees from Germany, mainly, who lived in Westerbork before the war, before the Germans invaded.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When the Germans invaded and took over, they took over this camp, Westerbork, and decided that this was a good place for a transit camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And those Jews who were already there, the Jewish refugees, German refugees-- they already lived there and they stayed there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they had the best places.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were houses.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were houses in Westerbork, and these German refugees lived in houses, whereas later arrivals all had to live in barracks.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had all sorts of preferential treatments.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
